The game must be responsive with minimal input delays.
The game must use simplistic 2d physics for mechanics.
Various sound effects must vary depending on interactions.
Enemies/obstacles of various types must be present in each level.
The game must display the score, time, and level in real time.
The game must track the players score.
The game must increase in difficulty per level.
Enemies and obstacles must move in predesigned movement patterns.
Character movement mechanics must be created.
The game must offer various powerups for the character to use.
The game must exit and reset when player encounters game over.
The game must contain a main menu screen.
